# ctf_monitor_metric_server
--------------

    Suits only for ubuntu, installing elasticsearch, kibana, metricbeat, making metricbeat to redirect all data locally and remotely to kibana dashboard

# ctf_monitor_metric_client
--------------

    Suits for both centos8 and ubuntu version, installing metricbeat, setting metribeat.yml to configure elasticsearch database as logserver:9200, and starting metricbeat service 

# ctf_monitor_log_server
--------------

    Suits only for ubuntu, installing default-jre and logstash, open logstash collection port 514

# ctf_monitor_log_client
--------------

    Suits for any Linux Didstribution, configuring /etc/rsyslog.d/50-default.conf to redirect its own syslog to remote logserver and restarting service rsyslog
